FBIS3-22065 "jptdd013__l94068" JPRS-tdd-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 21 March 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA EGYPT Antidrug `Campaigns' Locate 106 Poppy Farms in Sinai NC2403174594 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 21 Mar 94 p 2 NC2403174594 Cairo AL-WAFD Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Report by Muhammad Zaki] [Text] The Interior Ministry's Antinarcotics Department yesterday launched a large-scale campaign in the valleys of south Sinai. Some 42 poppy farms, 50 kg of bango [Egyptian slang for hashish], and 15 kg of dry poppy seeds were discovered and seized in the north of the Saint Catherine district. In a campaign involving the Public, Central Security, and Armed Forces, 27 cannabis and poppy farms were discovered in the south of Saint Catherine. For the first time, the troops involved in the campaigns sprayed the illegal poppy and cannabis farms from the air. Large narcotic plantations throughout the area were sprayed. Some 106 poppy plantations were found in the two raids. The troops are continuing their clampdown on drug farms in the region.
